<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 29 at 5:25PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Wayne, southern
Oakland and southern Macomb Counties through 615 PM EDT...
At 524 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorm over
Livonia, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Warren, Livonia, Troy, Southfield, Taylor, St. Clair Shores, Pontiac,
Novi, Romulus, Mount Clemens, New Baltimore, Flat Rock, Milford,
Grosse Pointe, Downtown Detroit, Canton, Detroit, Sterling Heights,
Dearborn and Royal Oak.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
southeastern Michigan.</instruction>
